From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keeley Hammond <vertedinde@electronjs.org>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 20:55:37 +0000
Subject: feat: surface global shortcut registration results to embedders

The GlobalShortcuts portal's BindShortcuts call is asynchronous and
consent-gated, but its result currently dies as a LOG(ERROR) in
GlobalAcceleratorListenerLinux, so embedders that expose shortcut
registration as an API cannot report portal denials to callers.

Add GlobalAcceleratorListener::SetRegistrationResolvedCallback and
invoke it from the Linux portal listener when a registration attempt
resolves: bind success or failure (scoped to the groups in that bind
request), session creation failure, portal unavailable, or already
bound in a previous session.

Also fixes two stalls in the existing state machine that the callback
made visible: the already-bound path now moves bind_state_ to kBound so
later registrations trigger a rebind instead of being dropped, and a
failed bind now closes the session so a retry attempts a fresh bind
instead of queueing forever.

This patch should be submitted upstream.

diff --git a/ui/base/accelerators/global_accelerator_listener/global_accelerator_listener.h b/ui/base/accelerators/global_accelerator_listener/global_accelerator_listener.h
index a48b7b73508942cc05e0dcf0fe108313f265c7c6..ed5f8cdd054a557a672a5bc1eb8def33ec544706 100644
--- a/ui/base/accelerators/global_accelerator_listener/global_accelerator_listener.h
+++ b/ui/base/accelerators/global_accelerator_listener/global_accelerator_listener.h
@@ -85,6 +85,18 @@ class GlobalAcceleratorListener {
       base::RepeatingCallback<void(const std::string&, const std::string&)>
           execute_command) {}
 
+  // Invoked with `accelerator_group_id` and whether the registration is
+  // actually bound, once an externally-handled registration resolves (e.g.
+  // the GlobalShortcuts portal accepts or denies a bind). May be invoked
+  // multiple times per group since re-binds re-resolve existing
+  // registrations. Only meaningful when IsRegistrationHandledExternally()
+  // returns true; the default implementation drops the callback.
+  using RegistrationResolvedCallback =
+      base::RepeatingCallback<void(const std::string& accelerator_group_id,
+                                   bool bound)>;
+  virtual void SetRegistrationResolvedCallback(
+      RegistrationResolvedCallback callback) {}
+
   // Removes command map entries whose execute_command callbacks are cancelled.
   virtual void PruneStaleCommands() {}
 
